hi this might be over sharing, but if it can inspire or help at least one person reading this, then i’ll take that as a win. 
let’s jump right into it 🤸🏼‍♂️

i have struggled with being vulnerable, trusting others and opening up to the ones i love. i have come to realize that these things are very important in  relationships - whether that be with a family member, bf/gf or friend. 

I started talking to a therapist (therapy is cool i promise) and it’s amazing to get a professional perspective on the way i think and how my mind works. Did you know you can change the way you feel & your thoughts create your emotions, and that you can control your thoughts. Learning that has changed the game for me. 

SO with all that being said, I challenge you to dive deep into yourself and really get to know who you are. see your self esteem & confidence flourish and you will become the best version of yourself. 🩵🤸🏼‍♂️
